# Contracts as Zod = Single Source of Truth

## 1. Purpose

Every type that crosses a layer boundary or runtime boundary (HTTP, vendor SDK, queue, AI response) is defined as a zod schema in `contracts/` (pre-migration `zedos/nextjs_space/src/contracts/`; post-migration `packages/contracts/`). Types are inferred via `z.infer` — never hand-written.

This rule complements:

- `.cursor/rules/72-hexagonal-boundaries.mdc` — `contracts/` may import only `shared/`
- `.cursor/rules/73-result-rop.mdc` — failed zod parse → `err(new ValidationError(...))`
- `.cursor/agents/execution/event-contracts.md` — agent that designs and reviews zod schemas

---

## 2. The contract

| Boundary crossed | Schema responsible |
|---|---|
| HTTP request → application | `<Resource>RequestSchema` in `contracts/<resource>/` |
| Application → HTTP response | `<Resource>DTOSchema` in `contracts/<resource>/` (validate before sending) |
| Vendor SDK response → infrastructure | `<Vendor><Operation>ResponseSchema` in `contracts/<vendor>/` |
| AI streamed JSON → infrastructure | `<AIOperation>ResponseSchema` in `contracts/ai/` |
| Domain event → consumer | `<Event>Schema` in `contracts/<context>/events.ts` |
| Form input → component → request | The same `<Resource>RequestSchema` reused on the client |

A type that crosses any of these boundaries without a zod schema is a violation. `event-contracts` agent + `reviewer` flag it.

---

## 3. Contracts structure

```
src/contracts/
├── shared/
│   └── common.ts          # Shared schemas (ids, pagination)
├── project/
│   ├── create.ts          # CreateProjectRequest, ProjectDTO
│   ├── update.ts          # UpdateProjectRequest
│   └── index.ts
├── payments/
│   ├── checkout.ts        # CheckoutSessionRequest, SessionDTO
│   └── index.ts
├── ai/
│   ├── clarification.ts   # ClarifyRequest, ClarifyResponse
│   └── index.ts
└── index.ts               # Re-exports all
```

